===========================================================
HIGH LEVEL FLOW
===============

Download API Request
→ Persist batch/download job
→ Publish lightweight Pub/Sub message
→ Worker consumes message
→ Fetch data in chunks
→ Incrementally append CSV
→ Upload/store file in GCP cloud storage
→ Update job status
→ Generate downloadable URL

===========================================================
PUB/SUB REQUIREMENTS
====================

Use Google Pub/Sub for asynchronous processing.

API layer should publish lightweight messages only.

Example payload:

{
"jobId": "...",
"screenName": "...",
"entityNames": [...],
"filterConditions": {...},
"selectedIds": [...],
"requestedBy": "...",
"metadata": {...}
}

Worker responsibilities:

* consume message
* process export safely
* support retries
* support idempotency
* support Pub/Sub redelivery safely

===========================================================
VERY IMPORTANT VALIDATION RULES
===============================

1. filterConditions and selectedIds are OPTIONAL.

2. If:

   * filterConditions == null
     AND
   * selectedIds == null

   THEN:
   fetch default dataset up to maximum allowed limit.

3. MAXIMUM EXPORT LIMIT:
   500000 records only.

4. If matching records exceed 500k:
   export ONLY first 500k records safely.

5. NEVER attempt to export beyond 500k records in a single request.

6. Make limits configurable.

===========================================================
DATA FETCHING REQUIREMENTS
==========================

Support these scenarios:

CASE 1:
selectedIds present
→ export only selected records

CASE 2:
filterConditions present
→ export filtered records

CASE 3:
both null
→ export default dataset capped at 500k

CASE 4:
both present
→ selectedIds should take precedence where applicable

